title: Splendours of the East - Temples, Tombs, Palaces and Fortresses
description:
pdf / English / 1965 / Putnam / 288 pages / 65 MB

Sir Motimer wheeler was Director general of the Archaeological Survey of India for almost 4 years. He studied ancients sites in that area and discovered a lot of material blonging to Indus valley civilization, he knows what he is talking about and you will not be dissapointed. I did not expect this book to have all these beautiful pictures but it was a nice surprise. The book covers all major regoins in that area of the world and information provided is very useful. (Amazon)
